cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless network analysis and design. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the computation of throughputs and optimal system utility. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a BP-adaptive CSMA algorithm. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) could be relevant as the paper discusses a distributed implementation of the BP and GBP algorithms. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also possible as the paper discusses distributed implementation of the algorithms.
